Sentencas: A nanocomposite, containing gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC, Ce0.85Gd0.15O1.925) and 10 mol% gadolinium-doped barium cerate (BGC, BaCe0.85Gd0.15O2.925), was developed as an electrolyte material for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The composite powder was synthesized through an auto-combustion process that yielded the desired phases right after combustion.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The powder was characterized using X-ray diffraction, particle size analysis, Brunauer-Emmett-Teller surface area analysis and transmission electron microscopy.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The electrical properties of the composite electrolyte were characterized by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy under air as a function of temperature.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The effect of second phase on total conductivity and activation energy of the composite material was compared with that of GDC of similar composition.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: For this, GDC (Ce0.85Gd0.15O1.925) powder was produced using a similar processing technique.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The microstructural characterization of GDC and GDC-10BGC composite materials was studied through scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of planar cell, using GDC-10BGC as electrolyte and employing Ni-(GDC-10BGC) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-based anode and cathode materials, were investigated.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinium-doped ceria and barium cerate-based composite electrolyte material for IT-SOFC
